00:16:15,750 --> 00:16:18,460
No, no. Go. I...

264
00:16:19,000 --> 00:16:22,000
You being here doesn't help me.
I'm sorry I'm like this, but...

265
00:16:22,880 --> 00:16:27,750
I need to be alone, figure out what to do.
You being here doesn't help me.

266
00:16:28,040 --> 00:16:30,170
Maybe I should go and Adi should stay?

267
00:16:30,790 --> 00:16:32,920
No, no. Both of you leave.

268
00:16:35,880 --> 00:16:37,040
Please.

269
00:16:43,540 --> 00:16:46,920
-Shir Ripin?
-Yes, come in, please.

270
00:16:52,380 --> 00:16:54,080
Your husband's home?

271
00:16:54,330 --> 00:16:56,000
No.

272
00:16:56,750 --> 00:16:59,420
-Do you know where he is?
-No.

273
00:17:01,040 --> 00:17:03,000
Okay. Tell us what happened.

274
00:17:03,630 --> 00:17:05,460
Do you want something to drink?

275
00:17:05,960 --> 00:17:08,330
-Water.
-Okay.

276
00:17:21,460 --> 00:17:23,250
What happened is my husband's missing.

277
00:17:24,500 --> 00:17:25,330
I...

278
00:17:26,130 --> 00:17:30,420
I called the police and they said a person
is considered missing only after 24 hours,

279
00:17:30,500 --> 00:17:33,250
unless there's immediate danger.

280
00:17:33,420 --> 00:17:37,710
I know something happened to him.
They said you get many calls like this.

281
00:17:37,790 --> 00:17:38,880
-Excuse me.
-So, I didn't...

282
00:17:39,460 --> 00:17:42,040
You called the police to complain
that your husband hit you.

283
00:17:42,960 --> 00:17:45,420
Yes. I needed to get you here.

284
00:17:46,420 --> 00:17:49,040
When I said he's missing,
no one took me seriously.

285
00:17:49,130 --> 00:17:51,710
So, did your husband hit you, or not?

286
00:17:52,710 --> 00:17:54,080
No, he didn't hit me.

287
00:17:55,170 --> 00:17:58,330
-I don't understand. Do you understand?
-No.

288
00:18:00,130 --> 00:18:01,460
What happened is...

289
00:18:03,540 --> 00:18:04,750
I was asleep.

290
00:18:05,040 --> 00:18:08,040
He took the dog for a walk.
The dog came back, my husband didn't.

291
00:18:08,130 --> 00:18:09,170
I don't know where he is.

292
00:18:09,830 --> 00:18:12,830
All his stuff is here.
His cellphone, his wallet, his moped.

293
00:18:13,580 --> 00:18:15,040
Everything's here. He disappeared.

294
00:18:15,130 --> 00:18:17,460
Something must have happened
when he was walking the dog.

295
00:18:17,750 --> 00:18:18,580
Do you understand?

296
00:18:19,380 --> 00:18:21,080
So why did you call and said he hit you?

297
00:18:25,210 --> 00:18:27,830
Well... I wanted you to come here.

298
00:18:28,500 --> 00:18:31,790
-When I said missing, no one took me...
-This won't help you.

299
00:18:33,670 --> 00:18:37,210
You think we'll go out to the street
to look for him, since we're here?

300
00:18:38,540 --> 00:18:40,580
I thought you might do something.

301
00:18:41,380 --> 00:18:43,880
It was useless calling on the phone.

302
00:18:44,880 --> 00:18:49,130
The secretary...
The police woman I spoke to on the phone.

303
00:18:49,210 --> 00:18:51,540
She didn't listen to me.
She didn't believe it was serious.

304
00:18:51,630 --> 00:18:55,710
So, you decided to lie a bit?
To press false charges?

305
00:18:56,710 --> 00:18:58,790
-It's not false charges.
-Yes, it is.

306
00:18:59,290 --> 00:19:03,830
Complaining about something that didn't
happen is the definition of false charges.

307
00:19:05,000 --> 00:19:07,380
You called the police
and said your husband hit you.

308
00:19:08,420 --> 00:19:10,960
For no reason. Just because
that's what you felt like saying.

309
00:19:12,080 --> 00:19:14,790
Do you understand that the things
you say have consequences?

310
00:19:15,210 --> 00:19:18,920
Significance? Do you understand
the meaning of a false complaint?

311
00:19:20,000 --> 00:19:23,790
Do you understand how much harm
it can cause to a person's life? Career?

312
00:19:23,880 --> 00:19:25,130
Do you understand or don't you?

313
00:19:26,170 --> 00:19:29,670
While your husband is supposedly missing,
you're sitting here drinking wine.

314
00:19:31,290 --> 00:19:35,920
The wine is... My friends poured it

315
00:19:36,500 --> 00:19:39,210
before I even told them. Forget the wine.

316
00:19:39,380 --> 00:19:41,290
42. Copy.

317
00:19:41,580 --> 00:19:43,250
This is 42.

318
00:19:43,540 --> 00:19:45,920
-So, you told them and they left?
-We're a bit delayed.

319
00:19:46,080 --> 00:19:47,170
Everything alright?

320
00:19:47,250 --> 00:19:49,580
-I'll get back to you soon.
-Because I asked them to leave.

321
00:19:49,670 --> 00:19:51,420
I felt uncomfortable with them being here.

322
00:19:52,000 --> 00:19:55,080
I understand. Why did you say he hit you?

323
00:19:56,920 --> 00:19:58,460
I told you already.

324
00:19:58,710 --> 00:20:00,960
I'm asking why you chose
to say that of all things.

325
00:20:01,670 --> 00:20:03,170
You could've made up a different lie.

326
00:20:04,960 --> 00:20:07,830
I thought it would get you here faster.

327
00:20:09,000 --> 00:20:13,960
If you'd said a rapist is trying to break
in, we'd get here even faster, right?

328
00:20:15,790 --> 00:20:17,290
I guess so.

329
00:20:17,880 --> 00:20:20,250
-But you didn't think of that?
-No, I didn't think of that.

330
00:20:20,330 --> 00:20:22,580
What you thought to say
is that your husband hit you.

331
00:20:23,380 --> 00:20:25,130
-Yes.
-So why?

332
00:20:29,130 --> 00:20:31,040
I don't know why. No reason. I don't know.

333
00:20:31,130 --> 00:20:32,880
Maybe because the reason I needed you is

334
00:20:32,960 --> 00:20:35,580
my husband, so I made up something about
my husband. I don't know.

335
00:20:36,080 --> 00:20:38,130
-What difference does it make?
-He didn't hit you?

336
00:20:38,880 --> 00:20:41,580
No, no, he didn't hit me.
I don't understand what you want.

337
00:20:41,670 --> 00:20:43,210
He never hit you?

338
00:20:43,290 --> 00:20:45,540
No, no! He never hit me!

339
00:20:45,710 --> 00:20:46,880
Are you sure?

340
00:20:49,210 --> 00:20:50,960
I don't understand what you want from me.

341
00:20:51,380 --> 00:20:53,710
Your husband has a history of violence
towards women.

342
00:20:56,580 --> 00:20:57,790
I don't understand.

343
00:20:58,750 --> 00:21:01,040
He hit a woman once
and she filed a complaint.

344
00:21:03,290 --> 00:21:05,000
-Rami?
-Yes.

345
00:21:06,290 --> 00:21:07,580
When?

346
00:21:08,170 --> 00:21:09,460
A few years ago.

347
00:21:11,170 --> 00:21:13,330
I think you're wrong. It...

348
00:21:13,830 --> 00:21:16,670
It sounds to me like you have the
wrong name or something. It's not...

349
00:21:16,750 --> 00:21:17,750
Adi Khalfi.

350
00:21:18,830 --> 00:21:20,130
Do you know her?

351
00:21:23,130 --> 00:21:24,380
Do you?

352
00:21:29,460 --> 00:21:33,290
Yes, she's his ex. I know her.

353
00:21:33,790 --> 00:21:35,500
She filed a complaint against him.

354
00:21:35,960 --> 00:21:38,500
He got mad with her once.
Punched her in the face.

355
00:21:40,580 --> 00:21:42,170
He didn't tell you that?

356
00:21:43,380 --> 00:21:45,170
Now you also complain he hit you.

357
00:21:46,040 --> 00:21:48,290
So, we get here and it turns out
he's not here.

358
00:21:49,130 --> 00:21:51,920
And you're claiming he didn't hit you
and that he's actually missing.

359
00:21:52,250 --> 00:21:54,790
You had friends here,
you sat here drinking wine

360
00:21:54,880 --> 00:21:57,330
while your husband's missing
at night, in the rain.

361
00:21:57,830 --> 00:22:01,080
This doesn't seem odd to you?
Do you find it odd?

362
00:22:05,920 --> 00:22:07,380
I've heard stranger things.

363
00:22:09,920 --> 00:22:12,540
Alright. When did he leave?

364
00:22:14,290 --> 00:22:18,330
I don't know exactly.
I was asleep at the time, but...

365
00:22:18,960 --> 00:22:21,380
I went to sleep at around 04:00-04:30 pm.

366
00:22:23,460 --> 00:22:24,460
What was he wearing?

367
00:22:28,920 --> 00:22:30,540
One moment, I'll check.

368
00:22:31,500 --> 00:22:33,170
Maybe I'll know from the jacket.

369
00:22:39,170 --> 00:22:41,710
Probably a leather jacket.
A black leather jacket.

370
00:22:43,830 --> 00:22:45,000
How old is he?

371
00:22:45,330 --> 00:22:46,790
35.

372
00:22:47,880 --> 00:22:49,080
Height? Weight?

373
00:22:50,210 --> 00:22:52,040
He's 5'8".

374
00:22:54,210 --> 00:22:58,000
I don't know. Maybe 155 pounds.
Maybe a bit less.

375
00:23:00,170 --> 00:23:01,790
Let me check something.

376
00:23:02,420 --> 00:23:03,540
Thank you.

377
00:23:04,080 --> 00:23:05,580
43. This is 42.

378
00:23:06,630 --> 00:23:08,080
43.

379
00:23:08,170 --> 00:23:10,000
Yes, copy 42.

380
00:23:15,830 --> 00:23:17,880
-Do you want to drink something?
-No, thank you.

381
00:23:20,500 --> 00:23:22,210
I'll make myself a drink.

382
00:23:47,670 --> 00:23:49,210
Why did you say he hit you?

383
00:23:52,880 --> 00:23:54,830
-I already told you why.
-I don't believe you.

384
00:23:55,830 --> 00:23:57,500
People don't just say things like that.

385
00:23:58,130 --> 00:24:00,000
Other things, maybe. Things like this, no.

386
00:24:02,290 --> 00:24:04,130
People say all kinds of things.

387
00:24:04,210 --> 00:24:06,130
All kinds of things,
but not things like this.

388
00:24:09,170 --> 00:24:11,540
I... I don't understand

389
00:24:11,630 --> 00:24:14,540
-why it matters to you so much.
-I ask the questions, you answer.

390
00:24:14,670 --> 00:24:15,500
This is how it works.

391
00:24:18,330 --> 00:24:19,170
Okay.

392
00:24:21,040 --> 00:24:24,420
-Who decided?
-I decided. I'm the police officer, right?

393
00:24:25,880 --> 00:24:27,380
I don't understand what's with you.

394
00:24:27,460 --> 00:24:28,710
What's with you?

395
00:24:29,420 --> 00:24:32,630
You call to say someone hit you
when in fact no one hit you.

396
00:24:33,130 --> 00:24:36,000
What's your problem? Do you want
someone to hit you, is that it?

397
00:24:36,290 --> 00:24:38,250
I don't understand what
you're talking about.

398
00:24:39,630 --> 00:24:40,540
What?

399
00:24:42,500 --> 00:24:44,040
Are you afraid of me?

400
00:24:45,540 --> 00:24:47,130
Are you afraid I'll hit you?

401
00:25:11,130 --> 00:25:14,170
You're... You're sick.

402
00:25:25,210 --> 00:25:27,960
He hit me once.
That's what you wanted to hear?

403
00:25:29,170 --> 00:25:30,210
He hit me once.

404
00:25:30,790 --> 00:25:32,630
He didn't really hit me.
It was a small punch.

405
00:25:32,710 --> 00:25:33,920
Bullshit.

406
00:25:35,500 --> 00:25:39,330
We had a fight, he tried to leave.
I stood in his way, so he tried to move me

407
00:25:39,420 --> 00:25:41,420
and he sort of punched me,
pushed me into the wall.

408
00:25:42,330 --> 00:25:43,420
Do you fight a lot?

409
00:25:45,750 --> 00:25:46,750
Like everyone else.

410
00:25:47,630 --> 00:25:49,210
What do you mean, "like everyone else"?

411
00:25:50,000 --> 00:25:50,880
Sometimes.

412
00:25:54,880 --> 00:25:56,000
Maybe he's not missing?

413
00:25:58,170 --> 00:25:59,630
Maybe he ran away?

414
00:26:00,250 --> 00:26:01,580
Maybe he was miserable here?

415
00:26:04,920 --> 00:26:07,000
Was there someone else?
Was he having an affair?

416
00:26:09,380 --> 00:26:11,460
You thought he was fucking
someone else on the side?

417
00:26:18,630 --> 00:26:20,420
Ma'am, I'm just doing my job.

418
00:26:21,130 --> 00:26:24,250
Your husband is missing and I need to ask
the questions that must be asked.

419
00:26:24,330 --> 00:26:26,920
-I don't understand what's your problem.
-I don't have a problem.

420
00:26:27,330 --> 00:26:28,710
You have a problem.

421
00:26:29,380 --> 00:26:33,210
That's why you called the police, right?
Now let the police do its job.

422
00:26:34,670 --> 00:26:37,080
Do you think there's a possibility
he simply ran away?

423
00:26:37,630 --> 00:26:39,880
Left everything and disappeared
of his own will?

424
00:26:41,960 --> 00:26:42,790
No.

425
00:26:45,380 --> 00:26:46,210
Okay.

426
00:26:46,630 --> 00:26:50,170
There wasn't anything out of the ordinary
in the area in the last few hours.

427
00:26:50,540 --> 00:26:52,960
No one matching his description
was brought to the hospital.

428
00:26:53,250 --> 00:26:57,420
If he doesn't show up before morning,
we'll open a case and begin searching.

429
00:27:03,670 --> 00:27:04,540
Hi.

430
00:27:04,880 --> 00:27:06,460
Hi, Doron.

431
00:27:06,960 --> 00:27:09,960
I thought that I should stop by.

432
00:27:11,130 --> 00:27:12,750
Pass through.

433
00:27:13,830 --> 00:27:15,670
-Come in, come in.
-Thank you.

434
00:27:19,250 --> 00:27:20,830
What a surprise.

435
00:27:24,080 --> 00:27:25,080
Have a sit.

436
00:27:25,290 --> 00:27:27,380
-Something to drink?
-Nothing, thank you.

437
00:27:32,000 --> 00:27:33,880
Are you sure you don't want
anything to drink?

438
00:27:33,960 --> 00:27:35,960
-Thank you. Really, nothing.
-Okay.

439
00:27:39,830 --> 00:27:40,670
Yes.

440
00:27:41,130 --> 00:27:43,170
-Okay?
-Yes, yes, sure.

441
00:27:55,080 --> 00:27:56,580
Maybe a beer?

442
00:27:59,080 --> 00:28:02,500
I don't think we have beer,
but we have wine.

443
00:28:04,380 --> 00:28:06,380
Red wine gives me headaches.

444
00:28:07,330 --> 00:28:10,210
-There's also whiskey or something.
-No, no.

445
00:28:10,830 --> 00:28:13,040
I thought a beer would go well
with the cigarette.

446
00:28:13,130 --> 00:28:15,500
-I'm driving and they're strict nowadays.
-Yes.

447
00:28:20,380 --> 00:28:21,670
How are you?

448
00:28:25,380 --> 00:28:28,920
Say, did you speak recently or something?

449
00:28:29,500 --> 00:28:32,540
No, we're not in touch. Not at all.

450
00:28:34,210 --> 00:28:37,830
Birthdays, we call to say congratulations.
Sometimes on holidays, but that's it.

451
00:28:37,920 --> 00:28:38,750
Yes.

452
00:28:39,210 --> 00:28:40,830
When did you last meet?

453
00:28:46,000 --> 00:28:48,420
A few years ago. He came to my show.

454
00:28:48,580 --> 00:28:49,750
You were there too.

455
00:28:49,830 --> 00:28:52,080
Yes, I was. It was a great show.

456
00:28:52,170 --> 00:28:54,210
-Thanks. Thanks.
-Yes...

457
00:28:54,290 --> 00:28:55,830
Those were good times.

458
00:28:56,380 --> 00:28:57,630
How are things now?

459
00:28:58,500 --> 00:29:01,540
We see you sometimes on TV

460
00:29:01,710 --> 00:29:03,080
and on the radio.

461
00:29:03,170 --> 00:29:04,790
Thank you. It's not what it used to be.

462
00:29:06,710 --> 00:29:08,580
But I'm getting by. It's okay.

463
00:29:09,170 --> 00:29:13,630
-How... You... You do...
-Shiatsu.

464
00:29:13,750 --> 00:29:14,790
-Shiatsu.
-Yes.

465
00:29:16,130 --> 00:29:17,710
It's going really well.

466
00:29:18,250 --> 00:29:21,460
I started working at this
great clinic in Herzliya.

467
00:29:22,460 --> 00:29:23,540
-Great.
-Yes.

468
00:29:23,630 --> 00:29:26,250
-Good, great.
-It's really good there.

469
00:29:26,790 --> 00:29:28,290
-Very good.
-Yes.

470
00:29:30,290 --> 00:29:32,540
He did stuff like this when he was a kid?

471
00:29:34,040 --> 00:29:35,000
What stuff?

472
00:29:36,130 --> 00:29:37,580
Go somewhere and disappear.

473
00:29:38,380 --> 00:29:40,880
No. No, not that I remember. He...

474
00:29:41,580 --> 00:29:45,380
He spent more time with his mom.
I was busy recording, performing.

475
00:29:45,790 --> 00:29:47,130
When we separated

476
00:29:48,000 --> 00:29:50,540
he was really little, 4 or 5 years old.

477
00:29:50,630 --> 00:29:51,460
Yes.

478
00:29:53,330 --> 00:29:55,420
-I apologize, I'm sorry.
-Hold on, I'll get...

479
00:29:55,500 --> 00:29:57,670
No, it's okay, I'll just get an ashtray.

480
00:30:08,880 --> 00:30:13,330
Really, he was a good kid. He was quiet
and serious. I remember

481
00:30:13,880 --> 00:30:14,830
that one time he even,

482
00:30:15,580 --> 00:30:16,920
I think it was a birthday,

483
00:30:17,790 --> 00:30:22,710
I gave him a guitar as a present
and he was so serious, played so well.

484
00:30:23,170 --> 00:30:27,210
So small that the guitar was bigger
than him. He could barely hold it.

485
00:30:30,670 --> 00:30:32,670
You think he...

486
00:30:33,920 --> 00:30:35,170
that something happened to him?

487
00:30:36,790 --> 00:30:38,830
I really hope not, but you know...

488
00:30:39,500 --> 00:30:40,540
I have no explanation.

489
00:30:40,630 --> 00:30:44,250
I don't even have a lead. I don't know.

490
00:30:47,420 --> 00:30:49,380
It's really weird, you know.

491
00:30:51,830 --> 00:30:54,080
You've been doing okay lately?

492
00:30:54,500 --> 00:30:56,460
Totally. Yes.

493
00:30:57,080 --> 00:30:59,630
And he wasn't stressed about work
or money or anything?

494
00:30:59,710 --> 00:31:02,130
No, everything was normal. I don't know.

495
00:31:05,580 --> 00:31:08,670
Listen, Shir, I have to go.
I'm expected somewhere.

496
00:31:09,830 --> 00:31:10,670
Okay.

497
00:31:13,500 --> 00:31:14,580
Thanks for coming.

498
00:31:17,670 --> 00:31:19,460
It's really nice.

499
00:31:21,080 --> 00:31:24,880
-It'll be okay. Everything will work out.
-Yes. Thank you.

500
00:31:48,580 --> 00:31:51,330
Shir, I thought I should
tell you something.

501
00:31:51,420 --> 00:31:52,830
Did you read something that...

502
00:31:53,750 --> 00:31:55,750
I don't know how to tell you...

503
00:31:57,330 --> 00:31:59,790
Look, he came to me

504
00:32:00,170 --> 00:32:04,880
one day a few weeks ago. He showed up at
my house and asked for money, a loan.

505
00:32:07,080 --> 00:32:10,000
And said he'll pay it back
in a few months.

506
00:32:10,290 --> 00:32:11,580
How much money?

507
00:32:14,330 --> 00:32:16,580
20,000 shekels.

508
00:32:17,130 --> 00:32:19,130
But the most important part is
he made me swear

509
00:32:19,210 --> 00:32:21,960
that if I happen to run into you,
I won't tell you anything about it.

510
00:32:22,040 --> 00:32:23,710
Did he says why he needed the money?

511
00:32:24,750 --> 00:32:27,460
He said that things are tight,
that he's not making enough money

512
00:32:27,540 --> 00:32:29,290
and you don't have enough work

513
00:32:29,380 --> 00:32:33,330
-and he didn't want to go to the bank.
-It's so weird. He has a ton of work.

514
00:32:34,210 --> 00:32:36,580
I've been making really good money lately.

