00:32:36,830 --> 00:32:38,670
I don't know. That's what he said.

516
00:32:38,920 --> 00:32:40,420
Did you give him the money?

517
00:32:40,880 --> 00:32:42,500
He's my only son, Shir.

518
00:32:45,380 --> 00:32:47,750
He said he'll pay it back in a few months.

519
00:32:48,830 --> 00:32:52,420
Why does he need the money?
What can you do with 20,000 shekels?

520
00:32:54,290 --> 00:32:58,790
I guess a lot of things. What can you do
with 20,000 shekels? Things.

521
00:32:59,460 --> 00:33:01,460
-What?
-Look, he came to me.

522
00:33:01,540 --> 00:33:04,500
He just showed up, asked for money.
I assumed you were tight for money.

523
00:33:04,580 --> 00:33:06,920
I gave him the money,
I didn't ask too many questions.

524
00:33:07,000 --> 00:33:08,960
Plus, he said he'll pay me back
in a few months.

525
00:33:12,830 --> 00:33:15,080
-Wait, I'll write you a check.
-No, no, no.

526
00:33:15,170 --> 00:33:18,420
-No, I don't...
-I don't know. We don't need the money.

527
00:33:18,500 --> 00:33:21,040
-I have no idea why he asked...
-I'm asking you, don't. No.

528
00:33:21,130 --> 00:33:22,460
-Wait a second.
-Forget it.

529
00:33:22,540 --> 00:33:24,380
It's not why I told you.

530
00:33:24,670 --> 00:33:27,080
-I came to tell you...
-Here it is.

531
00:33:27,250 --> 00:33:32,040
...the story. I don't... No. Forget it.
I'm shocked. I will not accept any money.

532
00:33:32,130 --> 00:33:34,000
Did he say he'll pay it back
with interest?

533
00:33:34,170 --> 00:33:38,460
You're acting crazy. Shir, I'm asking you.
I don't want any money.

534
00:33:38,540 --> 00:33:40,920
-It's okay. Wait a second.
-I'm asking you.

535
00:33:41,710 --> 00:33:44,460
This is really stupid.
This isn't what I meant.

536
00:33:44,710 --> 00:33:47,830
I'm not... Forget it.
I'm asking you, Shir.

537
00:33:48,380 --> 00:33:49,750
I just came

538
00:33:49,830 --> 00:33:53,710
-to tell you because I thought it might...
-I'm putting today's date.

539
00:33:53,790 --> 00:33:54,630
...somehow help.

540
00:33:55,000 --> 00:33:56,540
No, I'm asking you.

541
00:33:56,790 --> 00:33:58,540
No, I don't want it.

542
00:33:58,790 --> 00:34:01,500
No, I refuse. No, no.

543
00:34:01,580 --> 00:34:03,960
It's okay. Doron, take it. Doron!

544
00:34:04,330 --> 00:34:06,670
I'm asking you, Shir. I don't want this...

545
00:34:07,960 --> 00:34:11,920
-You're putting me in a tough spot.
-It's okay, take it.

546
00:34:14,500 --> 00:34:15,790
Everything's fine.

547
00:34:21,580 --> 00:34:22,920
Call me.

548
00:34:31,460 --> 00:34:33,500
-Tommy?
-It's me.

549
00:34:34,040 --> 00:34:36,210
Hi. Where are you?

550
00:34:36,670 --> 00:34:37,920
I'm here.

551
00:34:38,960 --> 00:34:40,130
Where "here"?

552
00:34:40,460 --> 00:34:41,380
Look out the window.

553
00:34:48,250 --> 00:34:49,130
Hi.

554
00:34:51,040 --> 00:34:52,500
Come on up.

555
00:34:53,580 --> 00:34:54,920
C'mon, Shir.

556
00:34:56,080 --> 00:34:58,080
-What?
-Are you serious?

557
00:34:59,380 --> 00:35:01,540
-You don't want to come up?
-No.

558
00:35:03,000 --> 00:35:04,420
So why did you come?

559
00:35:05,420 --> 00:35:06,580
Because you asked me to.

560
00:35:07,750 --> 00:35:10,460
I asked you to come because I need you.
I need you near me right now.

561
00:35:11,580 --> 00:35:13,130
Come be with me here.

562
00:35:13,290 --> 00:35:15,580
C'mon, we're going to stand together
on the street?

563
00:35:19,710 --> 00:35:21,130
Let's go to my place.

564
00:35:21,210 --> 00:35:22,500
I'm not going to your place!

565
00:35:22,710 --> 00:35:24,540
So, let's go eat.
I haven't eaten since lunch.

566
00:35:24,630 --> 00:35:27,420
I can't leave now. If there's some new
development, I need to be here.

567
00:35:27,750 --> 00:35:29,290
You mean, if he shows up.

568
00:35:32,580 --> 00:35:34,380
I'm not leaving this house,
do you understand?

569
00:35:37,080 --> 00:35:38,710
Come on up! I'm losing my mind!

570
00:35:39,130 --> 00:35:42,500
What if he shows up while I'm there?
What will you say, if he asks who I am?

571
00:35:44,040 --> 00:35:46,790
Maybe he's waiting for me to come up.
Maybe he's hiding behind a tree.

572
00:35:46,880 --> 00:35:49,290
Peeking out, waiting for me to come up
to catch us together.

573
00:35:49,380 --> 00:35:50,750
Stop talking nonsense.

574
00:35:51,580 --> 00:35:52,920
I'm serious.

575
00:35:53,000 --> 00:35:54,080
Come on up!

576
00:35:54,330 --> 00:35:58,000
I don't want him to know, I told you that.
I don't want to get mixed up in this.

577
00:36:00,380 --> 00:36:02,790
Oh, c'mon. Will you please come up?

578
00:36:04,170 --> 00:36:06,710
All I'm fucking asking you is to come up
and be with me.

579
00:36:07,080 --> 00:36:09,750
Look, Shir, I'm not coming up.
If you want, you can come down here.

580
00:36:12,920 --> 00:36:13,750
Coward.

581
00:36:14,960 --> 00:36:16,580
Fine, you can think I'm a coward.

582
00:36:16,670 --> 00:36:18,380
That's what you are, a coward.

583
00:36:18,460 --> 00:36:19,420
No, you're a coward.

584
00:36:19,500 --> 00:36:21,960
You live with a husband you don't love.
You're cheating on him,

585
00:36:22,040 --> 00:36:23,380
afraid he'll find out the truth.

586
00:36:23,670 --> 00:36:26,420
I don't want to get mixed up in this shit.
I told you from the start.

587
00:36:26,500 --> 00:36:28,210
Why do you think I don't love him?

588
00:36:28,960 --> 00:36:30,500
You do?

589
00:36:32,670 --> 00:36:34,170
It's none of your business.

590
00:37:04,210 --> 00:37:05,080
What?

591
00:37:05,170 --> 00:37:06,920
How do you know something happened to him?

592
00:37:07,130 --> 00:37:08,670
-Because I know.
-How?

593
00:37:08,750 --> 00:37:10,500
Because I know! I know him!

594
00:37:10,630 --> 00:37:13,420
That's what you think. He probably thinks
he knows you too.

595
00:37:13,500 --> 00:37:15,500
Quit the crap and come up already!

596
00:37:16,380 --> 00:37:18,080
Don't you understand it's a horrible idea?

597
00:37:18,540 --> 00:37:21,040
If I come up there and he shows up,
who knows what he'll do.

598
00:37:21,830 --> 00:37:23,750
What are you afraid he's going to
beat you up?

599
00:37:24,040 --> 00:37:26,630
Why should I get mixed up in this?
You have a fucked up marriage.

600
00:37:26,710 --> 00:37:28,670
I told you from the start,
I don't need this shit.

601
00:37:30,830 --> 00:37:32,580
You don't need this shit, but you need me?

602
00:37:34,710 --> 00:37:37,000
-Yes.
-Great!

603
00:37:37,710 --> 00:37:40,040
Great! Nice arrangement
you've got going here.

604
00:37:40,130 --> 00:37:41,710
You weren't exactly against it either.

605
00:37:42,040 --> 00:37:43,750
Tommy, listen.

606
00:37:44,790 --> 00:37:46,960
If you care about me, even a little,

607
00:37:47,880 --> 00:37:49,330
you'll come up.

608
00:37:52,960 --> 00:37:54,960
-You hear me?
-Yes.

609
00:37:56,630 --> 00:37:58,210
Don't leave me here alone.

610
00:38:01,500 --> 00:38:03,540
-Do you care about me?
-You know I do.

611
00:38:05,380 --> 00:38:06,500
So why don't you come up?

612
00:38:06,580 --> 00:38:08,420
Because it's fucked up!
Your husband's missing

613
00:38:08,500 --> 00:38:10,330
and I should sit with you
until he comes back?

614
00:38:10,420 --> 00:38:13,290
Feel sorry for you? Pretend I care what
happened to him? It's fucked up!

615
00:38:13,710 --> 00:38:16,580
You don't have to pretend. You can
rejoice, if that's what you feel.

616
00:38:18,000 --> 00:38:19,670
I don't feel that. Why would I feel that?

617
00:38:22,920 --> 00:38:24,330
You wouldn't want him to disappear?

618
00:38:24,670 --> 00:38:25,960
What do I have to do with this?

619
00:38:26,500 --> 00:38:29,210
Maybe you're happy, it's your right.
I have nothing to do with this.

620
00:38:32,580 --> 00:38:33,460
Say...

621
00:38:35,380 --> 00:38:36,290
you...

622
00:38:38,000 --> 00:38:39,290
did something to Rami?

623
00:38:41,330 --> 00:38:42,210
What?

624
00:38:43,080 --> 00:38:44,250
Did you do something to him?

625
00:38:45,750 --> 00:38:47,250
Why would I do anything to him?

626
00:38:48,420 --> 00:38:49,710
To be with me?

627
00:38:51,380 --> 00:38:54,460
You think I did something to your husband,
so that you and I can be together?

628
00:38:56,000 --> 00:38:57,670
I don't think anything. I'm asking.

629
00:38:58,000 --> 00:38:59,500
Listen. Darling.

630
00:38:59,750 --> 00:39:02,210
If I wanted us to be together,
it would've happened already.

631
00:39:02,580 --> 00:39:04,500
Your idiot husband has nothing
to do with this.

632
00:39:05,540 --> 00:39:06,580
Got it?

633
00:39:09,630 --> 00:39:10,920
Yes, I got it.

634
00:42:05,540 --> 00:42:12,040
Inside a wall stands a man

635
00:42:12,420 --> 00:42:18,080
All alone he stands in there

636
00:42:18,630 --> 00:42:24,710
Who knows the man in the wall

637
00:42:42,960 --> 00:42:48,920
The man's been standing
inside the wall since long ago

638
00:42:49,000 --> 00:42:54,920
He can't get out of here

639
00:42:55,130 --> 00:43:01,210
Who knows the man in the wall

640
00:43:18,750 --> 00:43:24,630
The man is small, the wall is huge

641
00:43:25,000 --> 00:43:30,790
The man is weak, the wall is strong

642
00:43:31,170 --> 00:43:37,210
Who knows the man in the wall

643
00:44:16,380 --> 00:44:18,040
Anybody here?

644
00:44:33,080 --> 00:44:35,330
-Mommy.
-Hey, sweetie.

645
00:44:36,330 --> 00:44:37,460
Wow, mom!

646
00:44:43,960 --> 00:44:45,920
-You were at the door?
-No, no.

647
00:44:46,920 --> 00:44:50,580
It was the neighbors, asking to turn down
the music. Said it's very late.

648
00:44:53,170 --> 00:44:56,210
-You saw me dancing?
-You danced beautifully!

649
00:44:56,630 --> 00:44:58,460
You always danced beautifully.

650
00:44:59,580 --> 00:45:01,250
And you sang beautifully too.

651
00:45:02,710 --> 00:45:04,130
Sing something.

652
00:45:05,420 --> 00:45:06,750
No, c'mon.

653
00:45:07,000 --> 00:45:10,250
-Why not?
-I'm embarrassed to sing.

654
00:45:15,580 --> 00:45:17,830
You're probably wondering
what I'm doing here.

655
00:45:19,580 --> 00:45:20,420
No.

656
00:45:21,460 --> 00:45:23,000
I know what you're doing here.

657
00:45:24,750 --> 00:45:27,830
I thought how nice it would be,
if you were here.

658
00:45:29,880 --> 00:45:32,750
But, sweetie, I can't stay for long.

659
00:45:35,420 --> 00:45:36,670
Why?

660
00:45:37,540 --> 00:45:39,330
I have things to do.

661
00:45:41,330 --> 00:45:42,790
What things, Mom? You're dead.

662
00:45:43,210 --> 00:45:45,000
Please, don't say that!

663
00:45:45,290 --> 00:45:48,250
Mom! Mom, I'm sorry!
I'm sorry! Forgive me!

664
00:45:48,710 --> 00:45:51,670
I'm sorry. I apologize.

665
00:45:55,380 --> 00:45:58,460
-Do you want to eat something?
-What?

666
00:45:59,040 --> 00:46:01,670
Do you want to eat something?
You haven't eaten all night.

667
00:46:02,380 --> 00:46:04,630
No, no. I'm not hungry.

668
00:46:04,710 --> 00:46:06,710
It's not good. You have to eat something.

669
00:46:06,830 --> 00:46:09,330
Let's see what you have
and I'll make you something good.

670
00:46:09,540 --> 00:46:12,670
Mom. Mom, I'm not hungry!

671
00:46:12,750 --> 00:46:14,290
Why is Rami not here?

672
00:46:15,290 --> 00:46:18,040
He needs to be here, take care of you,
make sure that you're eating.

673
00:46:18,290 --> 00:46:20,250
Leaves his drugs and walks away.

674
00:46:20,330 --> 00:46:21,920
-Enough, mom.
-It's not right.

675
00:46:22,130 --> 00:46:23,580
It's really not right.

676
00:46:24,960 --> 00:46:27,380
You have nothing in the fridge!
How can I make anything...

677
00:46:27,460 --> 00:46:29,830
Enough, Mother! I told you I'm not hungry!

678
00:47:12,000 --> 00:47:13,380
Bruno?

679
00:47:18,710 --> 00:47:19,920
Bruno?

680
00:47:27,670 --> 00:47:29,500
Bruno. My beautiful boy.

681
00:47:32,920 --> 00:47:35,330
Bruno, maybe you can tell me.

682
00:47:35,920 --> 00:47:36,960
Where's Rami?

683
00:47:41,830 --> 00:47:42,670
Maybe...

684
00:47:44,710 --> 00:47:46,130
Where is he?

685
00:47:46,750 --> 00:47:48,170
Where is he?

686
00:47:49,000 --> 00:47:52,170
Where is he? Answer me.
Where is he? Where is he?

687
00:47:52,330 --> 00:47:53,170
What?

688
00:48:24,630 --> 00:48:25,920
Anybody here?

689
00:48:33,380 --> 00:48:34,670
Anybody here?

690
00:48:37,000 --> 00:48:38,330
Who is it?

691
00:48:40,790 --> 00:48:42,080
Who is it?

692
00:48:42,380 --> 00:48:43,500
Who's there?

693
00:49:11,330 --> 00:49:13,040
It's for you. Thought you might be hungry.

694
00:49:19,880 --> 00:49:21,000
Can I come in?

695
00:49:39,790 --> 00:49:41,130
These helped you?

696
00:49:42,210 --> 00:49:43,080
What?

697
00:49:43,330 --> 00:49:45,040
The pills helped? You've calmed down?

698
00:49:46,420 --> 00:49:48,380
-A bit.
-How many did you take?

699
00:49:48,880 --> 00:49:50,540
-Oh, c'mon.
-Shir, how many did you take?

700
00:49:50,630 --> 00:49:51,460
Two.

701
00:49:52,130 --> 00:49:53,290
Two?

702
00:49:55,080 --> 00:49:56,960
I smoked a joint.
I had crazy hallucinations.

703
00:49:57,040 --> 00:49:59,250
You smoked a joint, took two of these
and you had wine?

704
00:49:59,330 --> 00:50:01,290
Please, let me eat in peace, okay?

705
00:50:04,210 --> 00:50:05,710
Is it good anyway?

706
00:50:13,750 --> 00:50:15,330
You're going to keep standing?

707
00:50:16,290 --> 00:50:17,670
Or maybe you'll take a seat?

708
00:50:24,750 --> 00:50:26,210
Why didn't you bring me a Pepsi?

709
00:50:26,580 --> 00:50:27,500
They didn't have any.

710
00:50:27,750 --> 00:50:28,830
So, get me some water.

711
00:50:55,250 --> 00:50:56,080
Thanks.

712
00:50:57,750 --> 00:50:58,830
So, this is where you live?

713
00:51:01,290 --> 00:51:02,130
Yes.

714
00:51:04,080 --> 00:51:08,210
Rami's study is there, past the bedroom.
You can take a tour, if you want.

715
00:51:42,540 --> 00:51:43,670
Nice apartment.

716
00:51:48,500 --> 00:51:49,830
You really think so?

717
00:51:50,210 --> 00:51:51,670
Yes. Nice apartment.

718
00:51:52,130 --> 00:51:55,080
I had a similar apartment when I was
your age. Not far from here actually.

719
00:52:05,040 --> 00:52:06,290
Come here maybe?

720
00:52:09,670 --> 00:52:10,710
Hug me.

721
00:52:26,080 --> 00:52:28,040
Thank you. Thank you, thanks.

722
00:52:47,420 --> 00:52:48,670
I knew you'd come.

723
00:52:49,250 --> 00:52:51,210
-You didn't know.
-I knew.

724
00:52:59,250 --> 00:53:02,130
It's so scary being alone.
You have no idea.

725
00:53:13,580 --> 00:53:14,710
Shir...

726
00:53:21,500 --> 00:53:23,920
Hey, Shir. C'mon, what are you doing?

727
00:53:34,630 --> 00:53:36,130
Caress me.

728
00:53:42,750 --> 00:53:43,580
Shir.

729
00:53:44,790 --> 00:53:46,670
-Open it.
-Shir!

730
00:53:48,170 --> 00:53:49,170
Open it!

731
00:54:18,750 --> 00:54:20,250
Get up! Get up!

732
00:54:26,380 --> 00:54:28,210
Go to the bedroom. Under the bed.

733
00:54:29,830 --> 00:54:31,500
Faster, faster!

734
00:54:33,420 --> 00:54:34,330
One moment.

735
00:54:50,080 --> 00:54:52,210
-Hi.
-Dudi!

736
00:54:52,630 --> 00:54:54,540
I called like a hundred times.
You didn't answer.

737
00:54:55,130 --> 00:54:55,960
Really?

738
00:54:57,000 --> 00:54:58,960
The battery probably died.

739
00:54:59,750 --> 00:55:01,670
Well, I'll check.

740
00:55:03,500 --> 00:55:05,630
-Weren't you up north?
-I was. He didn't return?

741
00:55:07,460 --> 00:55:08,290
No.

742
00:55:09,750 --> 00:55:11,170
Can I come in?

743
00:55:12,670 --> 00:55:13,540
Sure.

744
00:55:28,880 --> 00:55:30,330
Do you want to drink something?

745
00:55:31,170 --> 00:55:33,790
Yes. Tea maybe. I...

746
00:55:34,790 --> 00:55:36,250
I have a bit of a cold.

747
00:55:36,540 --> 00:55:37,630
There's no tea. We ran out.

748
00:55:40,630 --> 00:55:41,500
Okay, water then.

749
00:55:43,290 --> 00:55:44,580
Okay.

750
00:55:51,290 --> 00:55:52,170
So...

751
00:55:57,500 --> 00:55:58,750
Nothing. No news.

752
00:56:01,630 --> 00:56:02,960
What about the police?

753
00:56:03,330 --> 00:56:05,500
I talked to them.
There were no incidents in the area.

754
00:56:05,580 --> 00:56:07,000
No one was brought to the hospital.

755
00:56:07,460 --> 00:56:10,000
Nothing new.
They'll start searching tomorrow.

756
00:56:10,830 --> 00:56:13,710
-So what do we do now?
-Nothing. There's nothing we can do now.

757
00:56:18,710 --> 00:56:20,540
Nothing. We have to wait 'till morning.

758
00:56:21,710 --> 00:56:22,880
We can't wait 'till morning.

759
00:56:23,500 --> 00:56:25,210
-What do you want to do?
-Go look for him.

760
00:56:25,540 --> 00:56:26,750
-Where?
-Here in the area.

761
00:56:26,830 --> 00:56:28,790
The cops looked in the area.
Didn't find anything.

762
00:56:28,880 --> 00:56:30,540
You said they'll begin searching tomorrow.

763
00:56:30,670 --> 00:56:34,630
No. There were patrol officers here.
The extended search will begin tomorrow.

764
00:56:36,130 --> 00:56:37,710
You trust these patrol officers?

765
00:56:38,710 --> 00:56:40,460
Yes. I don't know.

766
00:56:41,210 --> 00:56:43,790
Okay, well, I don't trust them.
It's Friday night,

767
00:56:43,960 --> 00:56:47,670
-it's raining. They couldn't care less.
-I looked too, in the whole neighborhood.

768
00:56:49,170 --> 00:56:50,080
What do you think?

769
00:56:50,170 --> 00:56:51,040
So what do you want?

770
00:56:51,130 --> 00:56:53,500
That we'll just sit here
hoping for the best?

771
00:56:53,630 --> 00:56:55,000
There's nothing to do now, Dudi.

772
00:56:56,790 --> 00:56:58,580
I'll talk to you in the morning.

773
00:57:00,750 --> 00:57:02,380
-What's up?
-What?

774
00:57:03,540 --> 00:57:04,670
You're talking like it's...

775
00:57:05,710 --> 00:57:07,580
-Dudi, I did everything.
-Okay, forget it.

776
00:57:08,080 --> 00:57:09,960
-Where are you going?
-I'll do it by myself.

777
00:57:10,290 --> 00:57:12,630
Where... What will you do by yourself?
What are you doing?

778
00:57:12,750 --> 00:57:14,920
-If you don't care, you can sit and wait.
-What?

779
00:57:15,000 --> 00:57:16,920
-I can't do that.
-I don't care?

780
00:57:17,920 --> 00:57:19,630
-You have some nerve!
-Okay.

781
00:57:19,710 --> 00:57:22,080
-I don't care? You decided I don't care?
-Fine.

782
00:57:22,380 --> 00:57:23,380
-Go fuck yourself!
-Okay.

783
00:57:23,540 --> 00:57:26,630
Listen, Dudi, you can't come here
and talk like this in my house.

784
00:57:26,710 --> 00:57:27,750
-Okay, Shir.
-Get out.

785
00:57:27,830 --> 00:57:29,920
Shir, he might be lying
somewhere out there!

786
00:57:30,000 --> 00:57:32,880
Bleeding or dying or whatever!
And you want to sit here,

787
00:57:32,960 --> 00:57:36,420
-drink wine, eat noodles and wait for him?
-I told you, I already did everything!

788
00:57:36,500 --> 00:57:38,880
Okay, fine, Shir! I would've never
thought you're like this!

789
00:57:38,960 --> 00:57:40,210
-Like what?
-Okay, fine.

790
00:57:40,330 --> 00:57:42,630
Like what? You would've never
thought that I'm like what?

791
00:57:42,710 --> 00:57:45,250
What difference does it make now?
That's what's important now?

792
00:57:45,330 --> 00:57:46,750
-Yes, yes! Like what?
-Okay, fine.

793
00:57:49,460 --> 00:57:50,750
Dudi!

794
00:57:51,380 --> 00:57:52,290
Just...

795
00:58:04,290 --> 00:58:05,210
Tell me, Dudi.

796
00:58:06,750 --> 00:58:07,920
Is Rami seeing someone?

797
00:58:08,750 --> 00:58:10,580
-What?
-Is he having an affair?

798
00:58:13,710 --> 00:58:14,880
One-night stands?

799
00:58:16,580 --> 00:58:17,790
Are you serious?

800
00:58:18,000 --> 00:58:19,250
Damn serious.

801
00:58:22,250 --> 00:58:24,960
No, Shir. He's not seeing anyone. Okay?

802
00:58:26,290 --> 00:58:27,580
No one-night stands. No nothing.

803
00:58:29,920 --> 00:58:32,500
-As far as I know anyway.
-Who's Ella S.?

804
00:58:35,170 --> 00:58:37,250
Ella S. Look how many outgoing calls.

805
00:58:38,920 --> 00:58:42,080
-I don't know. Let's call.
-I called. Twice. No answer.

806
00:58:42,750 --> 00:58:44,040
Call again.

807
00:58:52,500 --> 00:58:54,000
Dudi, what did he tell you about me?

808
00:58:55,380 --> 00:58:57,790
-When?
-In general. You talk about me, right?

809
00:58:57,880 --> 00:58:59,330
The call is forwarded to voicemail.

810
00:59:00,920 --> 00:59:01,750
What did he say?

811
00:59:04,130 --> 00:59:05,380
Nothing special.

812
00:59:07,500 --> 00:59:08,710
And still...

813
00:59:10,500 --> 00:59:12,710
-Nothing. He said nothing.
-Nothing?

814
00:59:14,710 --> 00:59:16,330
Did he say he wants to leave me?

815
00:59:16,420 --> 00:59:17,250
No.

816
00:59:17,540 --> 00:59:18,380
Tell me the truth.

817
00:59:18,460 --> 00:59:20,750
-He didn't say he wants to leave you.
-So what did he say?

818
00:59:23,080 --> 00:59:25,330
Dudi. Talk!

819
00:59:28,920 --> 00:59:29,790
What?

820
00:59:29,880 --> 00:59:31,000
Nothing. He said that...

821
00:59:32,170 --> 00:59:33,670
He said you lost your sense of humor.

822
00:59:36,000 --> 00:59:37,170
What does it mean?

823
00:59:38,380 --> 00:59:41,170
Nothing. That when you met
you had a great sense of humor

824
00:59:41,500 --> 00:59:43,130
and lately it vanished.

825
00:59:44,880 --> 00:59:45,710
What?

826
00:59:47,040 --> 00:59:48,790
He told you a joke and you didn't laugh.

827
00:59:50,000 --> 00:59:52,460
-What joke?
-It doesn't matter, Shir.

828
00:59:53,420 --> 00:59:54,670
What joke?

829
00:59:55,330 --> 00:59:56,630
About mice and football.

830
00:59:57,920 --> 00:59:58,790
I don't remember.

831
00:59:58,960 --> 01:00:00,630
-It doesn't matter now.
-Tell me.

832
01:00:01,170 --> 01:00:02,330
What?

833
01:00:02,420 --> 01:00:04,460
-Tell me the joke!
-It's inappropriate now, Shir.

834
01:00:04,830 --> 01:00:06,420
I want you to tell me that joke.

835
01:00:06,580 --> 01:00:09,790
-Now? What for?
-Dudi, can you tell me the joke already?

836
01:00:15,830 --> 01:00:17,130
A man goes to the doctor, says,

837
01:00:17,210 --> 01:00:19,710
"Doctor, I've been having the same
weird dream for a month.

838
01:00:20,130 --> 01:00:21,880
White mice playing football."

839
01:00:22,330 --> 01:00:26,710
Okay? No big deal. The doctor says:
"Take these pills. Tomorrow it'll stop."

840
01:00:27,460 --> 01:00:31,460
So, the man says: "Thanks, doctor, but
I'll start taking the pills the day after.

841
01:00:31,540 --> 01:00:33,250
It's just that... tomorrow is the finals."

842
01:00:41,000 --> 01:00:42,750
-Remember?
-Yes.

843
01:00:43,670 --> 01:00:45,710
-You find it funny?
-Yes.

844
01:00:46,750 --> 01:00:48,710
This is what you talk about?
These sort of things?

845
01:00:48,790 --> 01:00:50,830
That I don't laugh at his stupid jokes!

846
01:00:51,580 --> 01:00:53,460
-About that too.
-Only about that, it seems.

847
01:00:53,580 --> 01:00:55,250
Cracking up, talking crap.

848
01:00:55,330 --> 01:00:58,460
Your best friend disappears and you have
no idea where he can be.

849
01:00:58,540 --> 01:00:59,960
-Oh, and you do?
-Dudi...

850
01:01:01,210 --> 01:01:03,170
Come, come. Get out.

851
01:01:04,670 --> 01:01:06,540
I'll call you in the morning.

852
01:01:06,630 --> 01:01:08,630
-No, no. I'm staying here.
-Dudi!

853
01:01:08,710 --> 01:01:09,540
No.

854
01:01:12,880 --> 01:01:14,000
You have no business here.

855
01:01:14,210 --> 01:01:15,380
It doesn't help me.

856
01:01:15,460 --> 01:01:18,130
I didn't come to help you. It's my friend
and I'm worried about him.

857
01:01:18,210 --> 01:01:21,540
-Do you have to worry about him here?
-You're afraid I'll know someone was here?

858
01:01:28,790 --> 01:01:30,000
He hates umbrellas.

859
01:01:30,420 --> 01:01:31,790
He never had an umbrella.

860
01:01:32,830 --> 01:01:35,080
It's Nadav's umbrella.
Adi's new boyfriend.

861
01:01:36,750 --> 01:01:39,630
They were here. I forgot they were coming
with everything that happened.

862
01:01:41,170 --> 01:01:43,540
So, you drank wine
and ate noodles with them?

863
01:01:44,040 --> 01:01:46,790
Yes, I was with them, eating and
drinking food and everything.

864
01:01:48,210 --> 01:01:50,500
-What do you want? That I'll stop eating?
-Okay.

865
01:01:51,040 --> 01:01:53,420
-I got it. I'm going to go look for him.
-Goodbye.

866
01:01:53,790 --> 01:01:55,000
-You're coming with me?
-No.

867
01:01:55,540 --> 01:01:56,920
-Why not?
-Because.

868
01:01:57,380 --> 01:01:58,420
What if he comes back?

869
01:01:58,790 --> 01:02:00,330
If he comes back, Shir, he has a key.

870
01:02:00,580 --> 01:02:03,210
He'll come in, see that you're not here
and he'll call you.

871
01:02:03,290 --> 01:02:04,630
And I want to meet him here.

872
01:02:12,040 --> 01:02:13,380
Tell me something. This Nadav...

873
01:02:13,920 --> 01:02:14,960
So?

874
01:02:15,460 --> 01:02:17,420
-What about him?
-He forgot his shoes too?

875
01:02:23,630 --> 01:02:24,670
Those are Rami's shoes.

876
01:02:32,420 --> 01:02:35,330
47? These are not Rami's.

877
01:03:19,830 --> 01:03:21,500
-I'm here. Come down.
-Hello?

878
01:03:22,290 --> 01:03:24,040
-Hello.
-Who is this?

879
01:03:24,830 --> 01:03:26,420
It's Shir. Rami's wife.

880
01:03:26,630 --> 01:03:27,750
Where's Rami?

881
01:03:28,170 --> 01:03:29,290
Who's asking?

882
01:03:29,630 --> 01:03:30,880
Tell him it's Ella.

883
01:03:31,830 --> 01:03:34,040
Ella, he can't talk now.

884
01:03:34,960 --> 01:03:36,460
Can you come up here, please?

885
01:03:36,630 --> 01:03:38,290
No. Where's Rami?

886
01:03:39,380 --> 01:03:41,460
He... He's not home.

887
01:03:41,790 --> 01:03:43,080
He called me.

888
01:03:43,830 --> 01:03:45,670
No, it was me who called you.

889
01:03:45,790 --> 01:03:46,960
What? Why?

890
01:03:47,630 --> 01:03:50,040
I wanted to ask you some stuff.

891
01:03:50,580 --> 01:03:51,880
Do you know who I am?

892
01:03:52,130 --> 01:03:53,580
-No.
-Sure?

893
01:03:54,040 --> 01:03:54,960
Yes.

894
01:03:55,040 --> 01:03:56,750
-Rami didn't tell you about me?
-No.

895
01:03:57,420 --> 01:03:59,080
Okay, so what can I do for you?

896
01:04:00,540 --> 01:04:02,130
Maybe you know where he is?

897
01:04:02,580 --> 01:04:04,330
I have no idea. Something happened to him?

898
01:04:05,330 --> 01:04:09,670
I think so. He disappeared.
Do you work together?

899
01:04:10,130 --> 01:04:11,000
No.

900
01:04:13,580 --> 01:04:14,790
What's your connection to him?

901
01:04:15,670 --> 01:04:16,960
What did you say your name was?

902
01:04:17,500 --> 01:04:18,380
Shir.

903
01:04:18,460 --> 01:04:22,130
Shir, sorry, I can't help you.
I have no idea where your husband is.

904
01:04:22,500 --> 01:04:24,830
Ella, you said you're here.
Why did you come here?

905
01:04:24,920 --> 01:04:26,170
I was in the neighborhood.

906
01:04:26,920 --> 01:04:29,750
Listen, Ella, I don't believe you,
so I want you to tell me who you are.

907
01:04:30,170 --> 01:04:31,880
It's none of your business. Bye.

908
01:04:32,040 --> 01:04:34,380
-I'm calling the police!
-What?

909
01:04:34,830 --> 01:04:37,540
I'm calling the police and I'm giving them
your number and your name.

910
01:04:37,630 --> 01:04:41,130
-I'll say you know something about Rami.
-Why would you do that?

911
01:04:41,540 --> 01:04:44,040
Because you won't tell me who you are.
You're hiding something

912
01:04:44,130 --> 01:04:46,000
and that something might help find Rami.

913
01:04:48,580 --> 01:04:51,250
Hello? Ella?

914
01:04:51,380 --> 01:04:52,960
Is there anyone else in the apartment?

915
01:04:53,630 --> 01:04:54,500
No.

916
01:04:54,580 --> 01:04:55,960
-Sure?
-Yes.

917
01:04:57,460 --> 01:04:59,880
-Open the door, I'm coming up. What floor?
-Second.

918
01:05:23,250 --> 01:05:24,630
What did you say your name was?

919
01:05:25,630 --> 01:05:28,080
-Shir.
-Shir. I don't know

920
01:05:28,170 --> 01:05:31,080
where Rami is or what happened to him.
I'm not his friend, not his lover.

921
01:05:31,460 --> 01:05:34,290
I have no idea where he is, so there's
no need to call the police, okay?

922
01:05:34,380 --> 01:05:37,130
Really? You get a call from him
in the middle of the night.

923
01:05:37,210 --> 01:05:39,330
You get here in 30 minutes
and tell him to come down.

924
01:05:39,790 --> 01:05:41,460
You're telling me
you don't know who he is?

925
01:05:51,960 --> 01:05:55,540
I didn't say I don't know who he is.
I said I have no personal ties to him.

926
01:05:55,630 --> 01:05:57,290
Okay? I sell him drugs.

927
01:06:03,000 --> 01:06:05,250
Look, I'm not a drug dealer.
I just have a few regulars.

928
01:06:05,920 --> 01:06:07,250
They call during my work hours.

929
01:06:07,330 --> 01:06:09,880
If everything's cool, I don't answer
and stop by within an hour.

930
01:06:10,750 --> 01:06:15,250
They come down, say "Hi", get the stuff,
we say goodbye. That's how it works.

931
01:06:16,380 --> 01:06:19,670
Rami is a regular. He called, I came.
Okay? Good.

932
01:06:21,880 --> 01:06:23,210
How do you know him?

933
01:06:23,580 --> 01:06:26,250
My brother's a musician.
Rami did some mix for him

934
01:06:26,460 --> 01:06:29,920
-or a cover. We smoked a bit, he liked it.
-He bought from you recently?

935
01:06:30,710 --> 01:06:32,000
Yes, about a week ago.

936
01:06:32,580 --> 01:06:35,670
-Is it pot?
-Pot? No.

937
01:06:36,210 --> 01:06:39,420
I don't do the small stuff.
Only the real thing.

938
01:06:41,000 --> 01:06:42,170
Which is what?

939
01:06:42,290 --> 01:06:43,380
You want to buy?

940
01:06:43,580 --> 01:06:45,170
-No.
-So, why do you care?

941
01:06:45,670 --> 01:06:46,790
I want to know what it is.

942
01:06:47,880 --> 01:06:49,750
I smoked something today that...

943
01:06:50,500 --> 01:06:52,170
Probably something Rami bought from you.

944
01:06:53,500 --> 01:06:55,330
I experienced weird things.

945
01:06:55,920 --> 01:06:58,540
Naturally! It's supposed to do
weird things. It's the real deal.

946
01:06:59,210 --> 01:07:00,330
So what is it?

947
01:07:00,420 --> 01:07:03,880
-You want know what it's called?
-For instance...

948
01:07:03,960 --> 01:07:07,580
It doesn't matter. Only I have it.
Trust me.

949
01:07:08,130 --> 01:07:10,920
-How do you know only you have it?
-I make it.

950
01:07:11,540 --> 01:07:13,000
What do you make it from?

951
01:07:13,170 --> 01:07:17,210
-Horse shit! What's with the third degree?
-Did he buy a lot from you?

952
01:07:17,290 --> 01:07:19,290
-Define "a lot".
-I don't know. In a week.

953
01:07:19,420 --> 01:07:22,330
What does it matter how many times a week?
The quantity is what matters...

954
01:07:22,420 --> 01:07:23,250
Okay...

955
01:07:23,880 --> 01:07:27,250
Is it measured in grams or what?
I don't know how this thing's measured.

956
01:07:27,330 --> 01:07:30,460
He didn't buy a lot. Average.
Said it helps him with work.

957
01:07:31,210 --> 01:07:32,540
Opens his hearing.

958
01:07:33,630 --> 01:07:35,080
So, it causes hallucinations?

959
01:07:35,210 --> 01:07:37,460
Only in the beginning. Then it works out.

960
01:07:38,580 --> 01:07:39,790
It...

961
01:07:40,250 --> 01:07:42,250
opens all kinds of stuff, you know?

962
01:07:43,670 --> 01:07:44,920
All kinds of stuff.

963
01:07:48,170 --> 01:07:50,080
You sure you don't want to buy?
I'm here anyway.

964
01:07:50,710 --> 01:07:51,710
Yes.

965
01:07:52,210 --> 01:07:54,040
You want to smoke together?

966
01:07:54,750 --> 01:07:57,000
-No.
-Well, can I smoke?

967
01:08:00,880 --> 01:08:02,000
-Okay.
-Good, great.

968
01:08:04,670 --> 01:08:05,580
I...

969
01:08:06,500 --> 01:08:08,040
basically hate apartments.

970
01:08:10,040 --> 01:08:11,540
Fucking hate them!

971
01:08:12,500 --> 01:08:14,080
It drives you crazy!

972
01:08:15,420 --> 01:08:16,460
Know what I'm saying?

973
01:08:17,580 --> 01:08:20,420
-Where do you live?
-In an apartment, where else?

974
01:08:20,750 --> 01:08:21,580
On the street?

975
01:08:29,290 --> 01:08:30,580
What's that?

976
01:08:31,500 --> 01:08:32,790
It smells like pot.

977
01:08:34,750 --> 01:08:35,630
Pot!

978
01:08:39,540 --> 01:08:41,750
Of course, I add a little.

979
01:08:42,170 --> 01:08:44,000
It's for the smell. Otherwise it stinks.

980
01:08:44,920 --> 01:08:47,000
Horse shit, I'm telling you.

981
01:08:48,130 --> 01:08:50,040
Is it expensive, this stuff?

982
01:08:50,710 --> 01:08:52,000
Define "expensive".

983
01:08:53,000 --> 01:08:54,880
Say, 20,000. How much can you buy?

984
01:08:55,960 --> 01:08:57,500
20,000 is serious.

985
01:08:58,920 --> 01:09:01,580
But... Rami didn't spend
that kind of money.

986
01:09:02,040 --> 01:09:04,250
-Are you sure?
-Totally, girl.

987
01:09:06,750 --> 01:09:08,000
You said you're his wife?

988
01:09:08,920 --> 01:09:09,790
Yes.

989
01:09:11,830 --> 01:09:13,000
Weird.

990
01:09:14,210 --> 01:09:15,580
He didn't tell me about you.

991
01:09:22,380 --> 01:09:23,210
Okay.

992
01:09:24,170 --> 01:09:26,500
-What?
-Never mind.

993
01:09:29,790 --> 01:09:32,130
Okay, fine. So what did he tell you?

994
01:09:34,290 --> 01:09:35,250
Forget it.

995
01:09:38,540 --> 01:09:40,000
Nothing, really.

996
01:09:43,250 --> 01:09:45,460
Don't worry, he didn't spill
his heart out to me.

997
01:09:46,500 --> 01:09:48,290
He only said it helps him.

998
01:09:48,630 --> 01:09:50,130
Opens his hearing.

999
01:09:51,210 --> 01:09:52,960
He didn't try to hit on me either.

1000
01:09:54,670 --> 01:09:56,000
He's cool, Rami.

1001
01:09:57,920 --> 01:09:59,540
So, what, he just disappeared?

1002
01:10:04,460 --> 01:10:05,290
Yes.

1003
01:10:06,830 --> 01:10:08,880
Took the dog out for a walk and...

1004
01:10:12,130 --> 01:10:13,960
Didn't come back. Disappeared.

1005
01:10:16,580 --> 01:10:17,420
So weird.

1006
01:10:18,880 --> 01:10:20,830
It's so weird that people disappear.

1007
01:10:21,880 --> 01:10:24,710
So weird! I saw this American TV show once

1008
01:10:24,790 --> 01:10:27,130
about a unit trying to
locate missing persons.

1009
01:10:27,630 --> 01:10:28,670
And there was this

1010
01:10:29,000 --> 01:10:30,880
-sort of...
-Was it?

1011
01:10:31,080 --> 01:10:31,920
What?

1012
01:10:32,540 --> 01:10:34,130
Could this stuff

1013
01:10:35,080 --> 01:10:37,540
do something like...

1014
01:10:38,080 --> 01:10:40,210
For someone like Rami, who smoked.

1015
01:10:40,830 --> 01:10:42,710
Could it have fucked up his brain?

1016
01:10:48,000 --> 01:10:49,960
That's the point.

1017
01:10:50,630 --> 01:10:53,130
What? Fuck up your brain?

1018
01:10:53,330 --> 01:10:54,540
Yes.

1019
01:10:55,330 --> 01:10:57,330
-Why?
-What "why"?

1020
01:10:57,500 --> 01:10:59,500
Why do you sell something
